---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { APP_NAME, DEVELOPER_NAME, ANDROID_PACKAGE_ID, IOS_BUNDLE_ID } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title={`Privacy Policy — ${APP_NAME}`} description={`How ${DEVELOPER_NAME} collects, uses, and protects your information when you use ${APP_NAME} on Android and iOS.`}>
	<main class="compliance-main">
		<div class="compliance-panel">

			<a href="/" class="back-link">
				<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="19" y1="12" x2="5" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"/></svg>
				<span>Back to Home</span>
			</a>

			<div class="page-header">
				<div class="icon-badge icon-badge--indigo">
					<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon--indigo"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
				</div>
				<h1 class="serif">Privacy Policy</h1>
			</div>

			<div class="prose-body prose">

				<p class="last-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 30, 2026</p>

				<section>
					<p><strong>Cats Build Ltd</strong> trading as <strong>{DEVELOPER_NAME}</strong> ("we", "us", "our") publishes <strong>{APP_NAME}</strong>, a mobile video app that helps you turn raw clips into polished social content by adding auto captions, motion graphics, and AI visual and sound effects on top of your footage. This policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use {APP_NAME} on <strong>Android</strong> (<code>{ANDROID_PACKAGE_ID}</code>) or <strong>iOS</strong> (<code>{IOS_BUNDLE_ID}</code>).</p>
					<p>By using {APP_NAME}, you agree to this policy and our <a href="/terms/">Terms of Use (EULA)</a>. If you do not agree, please do not use the app.</p>
					<p><strong>In-app consent:</strong> Before you use {APP_NAME}, we ask for your explicit permission to send derived video frames and audio to third-party AI providers for processing. You must agree in the app before any cloud AI processing occurs.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Information we collect</h2>

					<h3>Account information</h3>
					<p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Email address</li>
						<li>A unique user identifier</li>
						<li>Authentication credentials (stored securely by our auth provider; we do not store your password in plain text)</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Account sign-in is provided by <strong>Supabase</strong>.</p>

					<h3>User content</h3>
					<p>When you use the app, you may provide:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Video clips stored on your device</li>
						<li>Project metadata (timeline structure, effect settings, project names)</li>
						<li>Exported videos you choose to save or share</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Video files and project timelines remain on your device. We do not store your video library or editor projects on our servers.</p>

					<h3>Photos and videos on your device</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Import:</strong> You choose <strong>one</strong> video at a time through the system file picker (Files or, on iOS, your photo library). Only the clip you select is copied into the app. We do not scan or upload your entire photo library.</li>
						<li><strong>Export:</strong> If you save a finished video, it is written to your photo library (or shared via the system share sheet) at your request.</li>
						<li><strong>Permissions:</strong> iOS may ask for photo library access to import a selected video and/or save an export. You can deny access and still use other parts of the app, but import from the library or save-to-Photos will not work without the relevant permission.</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Cloud AI processing</h3>
					<p>When you use {APP_NAME}, derived content from your videos is sent to our cloud processing service and processed by third-party AI providers, including:</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Google Gemini</strong> (shot analysis, captions, and visual effect generation)</li>
						<li><strong>fal.ai</strong> (sound and media generation, including ElevenLabs and Lyria where applicable)</li>
					</ul>
					<p>We send:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Compressed storyboard frames derived from your video (JPEG contact sheets)</li>
						<li>Trimmed audio segments from your video</li>
						<li>Text prompts and technical metadata needed to generate captions, motion, and effects</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Reference frames derived from your video are deleted after processing completes. We do not use your content to train public AI models on your behalf.</p>
					<p>We may retain <strong>de-identified</strong> prompts, analysis text, and generated effect outputs in a shared technical cache to improve reliability and reduce processing cost. This cache is not linked to your account after you delete your account.</p>

					<h3>Purchase information</h3>
					<p>If you subscribe to Creator or Pro, payment is processed by the store where you subscribed:</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Android:</strong> Google Play Billing</li>
						<li><strong>iOS:</strong> Apple App Store in-app purchases</li>
					</ul>
					<p>We receive subscription status through <strong>RevenueCat</strong> (entitlement and renewal state tied to your account). We do not receive or store your full payment card number.</p>
					<p>Subscriptions are auto-renewing. Billing, renewal timing, cancellation, free-trial terms, and refunds are governed by the store where you subscribed and are described in our <a href="/terms/#subscriptions">Terms of Use (EULA)</a>.</p>

					<h3>Usage data</h3>
					<p>We record usage events to enforce monthly effect allowances and improve reliability, including:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Feature type (e.g. captions, VFX, SFX, shot analysis)</li>
						<li>Timestamps and quota debits</li>
						<li>Error and job status for generation requests</li>
					</ul>
					<p>We do <strong>not</strong> use this data for advertising. We do not sell your personal information.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>How we use information</h2>
					<p>We use your information to:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Authenticate you and manage your account</li>
						<li>Process AI features you request (captions, VFX, SFX, shot analysis)</li>
						<li>Enforce subscription plans and monthly effect limits</li>
						<li>Process subscriptions and restore purchases</li>
						<li>Maintain security, prevent abuse, and fix bugs</li>
						<li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>How we share information</h2>
					<p>We share information only with service providers that help us operate the app:</p>
					<div class="table-wrap">
						<table>
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>Provider</th>
									<th>Purpose</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr><td>Supabase</td><td>Authentication and database</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Google Cloud Run</td><td>Hosting our cloud processing service</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Google Gemini</td><td>AI analysis and generation</td></tr>
								<tr><td>fal.ai</td><td>Media generation (including ElevenLabs, Lyria)</td></tr>
								<tr><td>RevenueCat</td><td>Subscription management</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Apple App Store</td><td>Billing and subscription fulfillment (iOS)</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Google Play</td><td>Billing and subscription fulfillment (Android)</td></tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
					</div>
					<p>We may also disclose information if required by law or to protect our rights, users, or safety.</p>
					<p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Data retention</h2>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Account data</strong> (email, user id, subscription state) is retained while your account is active.</li>
						<li><strong>AI pipeline data</strong> tied to your account (generation jobs, shot analyses) is retained while your account is active.</li>
						<li><strong>Reference images</strong> from your video are deleted after each AI generation completes.</li>
						<li><strong>De-identified generation cache</strong> (prompts, analysis text, effect outputs without your user id) may be retained after account deletion to operate and improve the service.</li>
						<li><strong>Usage and billing records</strong> are retained as needed for quota enforcement and legal compliance while your account is active.</li>
						<li><strong>Video and projects on device</strong> remain under your control; uninstalling the app removes local app data.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
					<p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Access the personal information we hold about you</li>
						<li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
						<li>Request deletion of your account and associated data</li>
						<li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
					</ul>
					<p><strong>Delete your account in the app:</strong> Account → <strong>Delete account &amp; data</strong>. This removes your account, billing linkage, usage history, user-scoped AI data, and reference images from our servers. Local projects on your device are also cleared.</p>
					<p>You can also contact us at the email below for access or deletion requests (for example if you cannot sign in).</p>
					<p>You can cancel subscriptions anytime in <strong>Settings → Apple ID → Subscriptions</strong> (iOS) or <strong>Google Play → Subscriptions</strong> (Android). Account deletion does not cancel store billing. See our <a href="/terms/#subscriptions">Terms of Use</a> for full subscription terms.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Children's privacy</h2>
					<p>{APP_NAME} is not directed at children under 13 (or the minimum age required in your country). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we will delete it.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Security</h2>
					<p>We use industry-standard measures including encryption in transit (HTTPS/TLS) for data sent to our servers. No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure; we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>International transfers</h2>
					<p>Your information may be processed in the United States and other countries where our service providers operate. By using the app, you consent to such transfers subject to applicable law.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
					<p>We may update this policy from time to time. We will post the updated version with a new "Last updated" date. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Contact us</h2>
					<p>For privacy questions or data requests, contact:</p>
					<p><strong>Cats Build Ltd</strong> (trading as {DEVELOPER_NAME})</p>
					<p>
						Office 17907, 182–184 High Street North,<br />
						East Ham, London, United Kingdom, E6 2JA
					</p>
					<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@thinkingcats.com">support@thinkingcats.com</a></p>
					<p><strong>Terms of Use:</strong> <a href="/terms/">popmyvideo.com/terms</a></p>
					<p><strong>App:</strong> {APP_NAME}</p>
					<p><strong>Android:</strong> <code>{ANDROID_PACKAGE_ID}</code></p>
					<p><strong>iOS:</strong> <code>{IOS_BUNDLE_ID}</code></p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Store privacy disclosures</h2>

					<h3>Apple App Store (iOS)</h3>
					<p>When completing App Store Connect privacy labels, declare approximately:</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Data collected:</strong> Email, user IDs, product interaction, photos or videos (user-selected clip import, export to Photos, and derived frames/audio sent for AI processing), purchase history (via App Store/RevenueCat)</li>
						<li><strong>Photos or videos:</strong> Declare <strong>App Functionality</strong> for (1) reading the user-selected import clip via the system picker, (2) saving exports to Photos, and (3) derived frames/audio sent for cloud AI — linked to the user, not used for tracking</li>
						<li><strong>Data linked to you:</strong> Yes (account, user-selected video content and AI processing, subscriptions)</li>
						<li><strong>Data used to track you:</strong> No</li>
						<li><strong>Purpose:</strong> App functionality, account management</li>
						<li><strong>Third-party sharing:</strong> Google Gemini, fal.ai (and subprocessors) for AI processing</li>
						<li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Data encrypted in transit</li>
						<li><strong>Deletion:</strong> In-app Account → Delete account &amp; data; email fallback for locked-out users</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>Google Play (Android)</h3>
					<p>When completing the Play Console Data safety form, declare approximately:</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Data collected:</strong> Email, user IDs, app interactions, user-generated content (derived frames and audio sent for processing), purchase history (via Play/RevenueCat)</li>
						<li><strong>Data shared:</strong> With service providers listed above, including third-party AI processors</li>
						<li><strong>Purpose:</strong> App functionality, account management, fraud prevention, analytics (quota metering only)</li>
						<li><strong>Optional vs required:</strong> Account required for AI features; in-app consent required before cloud AI processing</li>
						<li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Data encrypted in transit</li>
						<li><strong>Deletion:</strong> In-app Account → Delete account &amp; data; email fallback for locked-out users</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
